### ==========================================================================
### GreenTrace Server — End-to-End Manual Test Suite (Phase 1–5)
###
### HOW TO USE:
###   1. Start the server: dotnet run (from GreenTrace.Server/)
###      Seed runs automatically: admin@greentrace.io / Admin@123!
###   2. Run requests top-to-bottom in order
###   3. After each LOGIN → copy accessToken into the matching @...Token variable
###   4. After each CREATE → run the follow-up QUERY to get the new ID,
###      then fill it into the matching @...Id variable below
###
### Schema explorer (Banana Cake Pop): http://localhost:5227/graphql
###
### TODO — Integration Tests (tackle after manual testing passes):
###   Priority paths to cover with automated tests:
###     - Auth flow (login, token refresh, logout, expired token rejection)
###     - Stage record lifecycle: draft → submit → validate (value record auto-creation)
###     - Stage record rejection → re-submit → validate
###     - Org-scoping: confirm one org cannot see another's data
###     - Analytics query correctness against known seed data
###     - Audit log entries written on every mutation
### ==========================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5227/graphql

### ─── Tokens (paste accessToken value after each login) ─────────────────────
@platformAdminToken = PASTE_TOKEN_HERE
@orgAdminToken      = PASTE_TOKEN_HERE
@fieldAgentToken    = PASTE_TOKEN_HERE
@validatorToken     = PASTE_TOKEN_HERE

### ─── Refresh tokens (paste refreshToken for Section 13) ────────────────────
@fieldAgentRefreshToken = PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

### ─── IDs — fill as you run through the tests ───────────────────────────────

### Org (seeded org = 1; test org we create = most likely 2)
@testOrgId        = 2

### Chain config
@domainId         = 0
@stage1Id         = 0
@stage2Id         = 0
@stage3Id         = 0
@stage4Id         = 0

### Stage fields
@sf_moistureId    = 0
@sf_fermDaysId    = 0
@sf_dryingId      = 0
@sf_transportId   = 0
@sf_receiptWtId   = 0
@sf_procWeightId  = 0
@sf_gradeId       = 0
@sf_destId        = 0

### Actor roles
@role_farmerId    = 0
@role_buyerId     = 0
@role_processorId = 0
@role_exporterId  = 0

### Actors
@actor_kofiId     = 0
@actor_amaId      = 0
@actor_kumasiId   = 0
@actor_goldstarId = 0

### Product & batches
@productId        = 0
@batchId          = 0
@batchId2         = 0

### Stage records
@sr1Id            = 0
@sr2Id            = 0
@sr3Id            = 0
@sr4Id            = 0
@sr_rejectedId    = 0
@sr_correctedId   = 0



### ==========================================================================
### SECTION 1 — PLATFORM ADMIN: AUTH & ORG SETUP
### ==========================================================================

### 1.1 — Login as Platform Admin (seeded)
# → copy accessToken into @platformAdminToken above
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation { login(input: { email: \"admin@greentrace.io\", password: \"Admin@123!\" }) { callResult { success message code result { accessToken refreshToken expiresAt } } } }"
}

###

### 1.2 — Verify Platform Admin Identity
# → expect role = platform_admin, full permissions list
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdminToken}}

{
  "query": "query { me { userId organizationId fullName email role permissions } }"
}

###

### 1.3 — List Existing Organizations
# → should show seeded org: GreenTrace (id=1)
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdminToken}}

{
  "query": "query { organizations { nodes { id name slug isActive createdAt } totalCount } }"
}

###

### 1.4 — Create Test Organization "Ghana Cocoa Authority"
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdminToken}}

{
  "query": "mutation { createOrganization(input: { name: \"Ghana Cocoa Authority\", slug: \"gca\" }) { callResult { success message code } } }"
}

###

### 1.5 — Query Organizations (copy new org id into @testOrgId above)
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdminToken}}

{
  "query": "query { organizations { nodes { id name slug isActive } totalCount } }"
}

###

### 1.6 — Create Org Admin User for Test Org
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdminToken}}

{
  "query": "mutation { createUser(input: { email: \"orgadmin@gca.io\", password: \"OrgAdmin@123!\", fullName: \"GCA Admin\", organizationId: {{testOrgId}}, roleName: \"org_admin\" }) { callResult { success message code } } }"
}

###

### 1.7 — Create Field Agent User for Test Org
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdminToken}}

{
  "query": "mutation { createUser(input: { email: \"agent@gca.io\", password: \"Agent@123!\", fullName: \"Field Agent\", organizationId: {{testOrgId}}, roleName: \"field_agent\" }) { callResult { success message code } } }"
}

###

### 1.8 — Create Validator User for Test Org
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdminToken}}

{
  "query": "mutation { createUser(input: { email: \"validator@gca.io\", password: \"Validator@123!\", fullName: \"GCA Validator\", organizationId: {{testOrgId}}, roleName: \"validator\" }) { callResult { success message code } } }"
}



