{
  "query": "query { batches { nodes { id batchCode status currentQuantity totalValue originDate } } }"
}



### ==========================================================================
### SECTION 6 — STAGE RECORD LIFECYCLE: BATCH 1 (Happy Path)
### 500kg farm → 480kg aggregation → 450kg processing → 450kg export
### Expected total value: 500×1.50 + 480×2.10 + 450×4.00 + 450×8.50 = ~$7,533
### Expected ValueRecords: 4 (one per validated stage record)
### ==========================================================================

### ─── STAGE 1: HARVESTING ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 6.1 — [Field Agent] Create StageRecord 1: Harvesting (status = draft)
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{fieldAgentToken}}

{
  "query": "mutation CreateSR($input: CreateStageRecordInput!) { createStageRecord(input: $input) { callResult { success message code } } }",
  "variables": {
    "input": {
      "batchId": {{batchId}},
      "stageId": {{stage1Id}},
      "actorId": {{actor_kofiId}},
      "quantity": 500,
      "unitPrice": 1.50,
      "currency": "USD",
      "geoPoint": "{\"lat\":6.688,\"lng\":-1.624}",
      "notes": "First harvest of the season. Good quality beans.",
      "recordedAt": "2026-04-20T09:00:00Z",
      "fields": [
        { "stageFieldId": {{sf_moistureId}}, "value": "7.2" },
        { "stageFieldId": {{sf_fermDaysId}}, "value": "6" },
        { "stageFieldId": {{sf_dryingId}}, "value": "sun_dried" }
      ]
    }
  }
}

###

### 6.2 — Query Stage Records (copy Harvesting record id into @sr1Id above)
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{fieldAgentToken}}

{
  "query": "query { stageRecords { nodes { id batchId stageId status quantity unitPrice recordedAt } } }"
}

###

### 6.3 — [Field Agent] Submit StageRecord 1
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{fieldAgentToken}}

{
  "query": "mutation { submitStageRecord(input: { id: {{sr1Id}} }) { callResult { success message code } } }"
}

###

### 6.4 — Login as Validator
# → copy accessToken into @validatorToken above
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation { login(input: { email: \"validator@gca.io\", password: \"Validator@123!\" }) { callResult { success message code result { accessToken refreshToken expiresAt } } } }"
}

###

### 6.5 — [Validator] Query Submitted Records (should see sr1 with status=submitted)
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{validatorToken}}

{
  "query": "query { stageRecords(where: { status: { eq: \"submitted\" } }) { nodes { id batchId stageId status quantity unitPrice } totalCount } }"
}

###

### 6.6 — [Validator] Validate StageRecord 1
# CRITICAL: This triggers automatic ValueRecord creation for this stage
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{validatorToken}}

{
  "query": "mutation { validateStageRecord(input: { id: {{sr1Id}}, validationNotes: \"Moisture content acceptable. Fermentation adequate.\" }) { callResult { success message code } } }"
}

###

### ─── STAGE 2: AGGREGATION ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 6.7 — [Field Agent] Create StageRecord 2: Aggregation
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{fieldAgentToken}}

{
  "query": "mutation CreateSR($input: CreateStageRecordInput!) { createStageRecord(input: $input) { callResult { success message code } } }",
  "variables": {
    "input": {
      "batchId": {{batchId}},
      "stageId": {{stage2Id}},
      "actorId": {{actor_amaId}},
      "quantity": 480,
      "unitPrice": 2.10,
      "currency": "USD",
      "geoPoint": "{\"lat\":6.700,\"lng\":-1.610}",
      "notes": "Received at aggregation point. 20kg transport loss noted.",
      "recordedAt": "2026-04-22T14:00:00Z",
      "fields": [
        { "stageFieldId": {{sf_transportId}}, "value": "truck" },
        { "stageFieldId": {{sf_receiptWtId}}, "value": "480" }
      ]
    }
  }
}

###

### 6.8 — Query Stage Records (copy Aggregation record id into @sr2Id above)
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{fieldAgentToken}}

{
  "query": "query { stageRecords(where: { batchId: { eq: {{batchId}} } }) { nodes { id stageId status quantity unitPrice } } }"
}

###

